array.string: "Live every day like it's Taco Tuesday."
"All I'm saying is you've never seen anyone crying and eating tacos at the same time."
"In case of taco emergency call 9 Juan Juan."
"Yesterday I really wanted tacos. Now I'm eating tacos. Follow your dreams."
"Taco dirty to me."
"When is taco-bod season, because I am ready for that."
"I'm in a good place right now. Not emotionally - I'm just at a taco stand."
"Pros and Cons Of Eating Tacos - Pros: Eating the tacos. Cons: Finishing the tacos."
"I want to start juicing but I'm hesitant because I don't know how to juice tacos."
"I oppose Taco Tuesday, only because it sends the message that other days aren't also for tacos."
"Inhale tacos. Exhale negativity. Namaste."
"Thank god I don't have to hunt for my food, I don't even know where tacos live."
"All I want to hear are those three magical little words...I brought tacos."
"Ideal date: We go get tacos. I eat 13. You are very impressed and not at all grossed out."
"If someone tells you that you eat too many tacos, just walk away. You don't need that kind of negativity in your life."
"I wish I was full of tacos instead of emotions."
"There is no WE in tacos."
""I hate tacos" - said no Juan ever."
"Fitness? More like fitness whole taco in my mouth."
"Life is short. Eat more tacos."
"Bathing suit season is just around the corner. Unfortunately, so is the taco truck."
"Don't tell me you miss me. Tell me you're outside with tacos. Actions speak louder than words."
"If you had to choose between being skinny or eating taco everyday - would you choose hard or soft tacos?"
"A well balanced diet is a taco in each hand."
"Make tacos, not war."
